Arrays
/+/ Similar to lists, to define an array 
/+/ Arrays are not objects

A simple example of an array:
int[] array1 = new int[3]; //new int [3] says that this array is size 3.
array1[0] = 10;
array1[1] = 20;
array1[2] = 30;
// these three statments set the three slots in the array to 10, 20, and 30. 

/+/ you can also initilize a list quickly by doing:
int[] array1 = {10, 20, 30};


/+/ Methods for arrays include:
.length //do not use() 

/+/ if arrays are not full make sure to keep track of how many of the values you are using. 
/+/ partially full arrays defulat to zero if you are asking for a value within the bounds of the array that has not yet been defined.

++++++++++++++++++
SPECIAL FOR LOOP
++++++++++++++++++

for(int i: array1) //This loops through values in the array. it is not as flexible but is quicker to type. 
  System.out.print(i);
 
String arrays
String [] names = {"Jackie", "Bob", "Lisa", "Jim"};

